law.catch_line: Cabinet is not required to prosecute.
law.text: Nothing in KRS 217.005 to 217.215 shall be construed as requiring the cabinet to report for the institution of proceedings under KRS 217.005 to 217.215, violations of KRS 217.005 to 217.215, whenever the cabinet believes that the public interest will be adequately served in the circumstances by a suitable written notice or warning.
